            <note xml:id="foot.f2">CD refers to his publisher, John Murray. Mivart had said that he did not have a copy of <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_7951.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Variation</hi></ref> (<ref target="./DCP-LETT-7458.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from St G. J. Mivart, 26 January 1871</ref>).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3">See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-7425.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to Francis Darwin, [after 21 January 1871]</ref>, n. 2, <ref target="./DCP-LETT-7453A.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to St G. J. Mivart, 23 January [1871]</ref>, and <ref target="./DCP-LETT-7458.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from St G. J. Mivart, 26 January 1871</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f4">CD also discussed ancon and Mauchamp sheep in <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_7951.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Variation</hi></ref> 1: 100.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f5">On niata cattle, see also <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_7951.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Variation</hi></ref> 1: 89–91.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f6">On turnspit dogs, see also <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_7951.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Variation</hi></ref> 1: 17.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f7">See also <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_7951.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Variation</hi></ref> 1: 230.</note>
